                        <h1>What is NDIS?</h1>
                        <p>NDIS stands for National Disability Insurance Scheme. It is a government funding scheme which aims to help people under the age of 65 with disabilities get the care and support they need.</p>
                        <p>It recognises that disability-related support is an entitlement, and means you have a choice of service providers in an open market – it gives you more choice and control.</p>
                        <p>NDIS also provides families and carers with the information they require about services to support people with disabilities.</p>
                        <p>For more information about the NDIS funding scheme, visit the <a href="https://www.ndis.gov.au/" target="_blank" class="text-success">official NDIS website</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="row mt-5">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <h2>Who is eligible?</h2>
                        <p>To qualify and become a participant of NDIS, people must first meet the access requirements.</p>
                        <p>These requirements are:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Availability of NDIS in your area</li>
                            <li>Your age</li>
                            <li>Your residency status</li>
                            <li>Your disability and in some cases your early intervention requirements</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>For information about access requirements, visit the <a href="https://www.ndis.gov.au/applying-access-ndis/am-i-eligible" target="_blank" class="text-success">official NDIS website</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
               
